[202.272608, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[H\u001b[38;5;246m● \u001b[39mUser\u001b[8Ganswered\u001b[17GClaude's\u001b[26Gquestions:\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m  ⎿  · When the DevPulse app is closed on a client machine, should ingestion \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B \u001b[4G \u001b[6G\u001b[38;5;246msources (watched folders/repos) keep flowing to clyffy? → Headless agent \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bfrom day one\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;5;246m· Clyffy-side: transport + session machinery always-on in EVERY resource \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bprofile (Lite-12GB up to 3-Spark ring), with profiles scaling only the \r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[4G  \u001b[38;5;246mmodel roster/funnel depth? → Yes — contract is profile-invariant \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;5;246m(Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;5;246m· Four-layer placement: transport/session seam = SURFACE concern (Brain API\r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[4G  \u001b[38;5;246msurface), with destructive-op gating expressed at the capability-pack \r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;5;246mlayer? → Surface owns transport; packs own risk-gates (Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;174m·\u001b[3G\u001b[38;5;180mConcocting…\u001b[38;5;174m \u001b[38;5;246m(2m 15s · ↓\u001b[39m \u001b[38;5;246m6.8k tokens)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m  ⎿  Tip: Use /btw to ask a quick side question without interrupting Claude's \r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;5;246mcurrent work\u001b[19G\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B                                                            \u001b[38;5;246m● high · /effort\r\u001b[1B\u001b[48;5;37m\u001b[38;5;16m dd:Read ~/.deepdive/dives/devpulse-l2-session/briefs/deployment-shape.md \r\u001b[1B(COSTAR brief) then begin \u001b[49m\u001b[38;5;37m──\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m❯ \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;37m───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────